  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        <div xml:id="KT83-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">talaimakaṉ varaintu eytal (C2: eytutal) uṇarttiya ceviliyait tōḻi vāḻttiyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">The confidante blessing the foster-mother, when she announced HIS approach for marriage.</p>
          </div>



        <div xml:id="KT83">
            <lg type="edition">
<l>                arumpeṟa lamiḻta mārpata mākap</l>
<l>                perumpeya rulakam peṟīiyarō vaṉṉai</l>
<l>                tammiṟ ṟamatuṇ ṭaṉṉa ciṉaitoṟun</l>
<l>                tīmpaḻan tūṅkum palavi</l>
<l>                ṉōṅkumalai nāṭaṉai varumeṉ ṟōḷē.</l>
             </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <l>May mother obtain the world of great name</l>
                <l rend="indent">[for her] to have to [her] fill of ambrosia, hard to obtain,</l>
                <l>she who said:</l>
                <l rend="indent3">he will come<note place="foot">Literally, with accusative: "who has said the man from the mountain as coming".</note>, the man from the high mountain</l>
                <l rend="indent">with jackfruit trees hung with sweet fruit</l>
                <l rend="indent">on every twig, eaten like one's own in one's own house.</l>
                <lg type="alternate" resp="#Srin" sameAs="1+2b">
               <l>May [the mother] be given ambrosia that is hard to obtain</l>
               <l>(that is, for humans, not for gods), [as] precious food (āka)!</l>
               <l>	(At least) may mother obtain the world of the famous...</l>
                </lg>

            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
